<i>noun</i>: 필기 [필기], 표기 [표기], 펜 [], 집필 [집필], 저술 [저ː술], 작성 [작썽], 작문 [장문], 쓰기 [쓰기], 글짓기 [글짇끼], 글씨 [글씨], 글쓰기 [글쓰기], 글 [글] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>필기 [필기]</dt><br>
<dd>1. writing; writing down</dd><br>
<dd>글씨를 씀.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of writing letters or words.</dd><br>
<dd>2. note; noting down</dd><br>
<dd>강의, 강연, 연설 등의 내용을 받아 적음.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of taking notes on the details of a lecture, speech, address, etc.</dd><br>
<dt>표기 [표기]</dt><br>
<dd>1. writing; marking</dd><br>
<dd>적어서 나타냄. 또는 그런 기록.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of expressing something by writing it down.</dd><br>
<dd>2. notation</dd><br>
<dd>말을 문자 또는 음성 기호로 표시함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of writing and expressing a speech in characters or signs.</dd><br>
<dt>펜 []</dt><br>
<dd>1. pen</dd><br>
<dd>잉크나 먹 등을 찍어서 글씨를 쓰는 기구.</dd><br>
<dd>An implement used to write letters after dipping it into ink or a mixture of water and ground ink stick.</dd><br>
<dd>2. writing implement</dd><br>
<dd>볼펜이나 사인펜 등의 필기구.</dd><br>
<dd>A writing implement such as a ball-point pen, marker, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>3. writing</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 글을 쓰는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) The work of writing.</dd><br>
<dt>집필 [집필]</dt><br>
<dd>writing</dd><br>
<dd>직접 글을 씀.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of writing something.</dd><br>
<dt>저술 [저ː술]</dt><br>
<dd>writing; book; publication</dd><br>
<dd>주로 학술적인 글이나 책 등을 씀. 또는 그런 글이나 책.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of mainly writing an academic article, book, etc., or such an article or book.</dd><br>
<dt>작성 [작썽]</dt><br>
<dd>1. writing; filling in; drawing up</dd><br>
<dd>원고나 서류 등을 만듦.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of making a script, document, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>2. setting a record</dd><br>
<dd>운동 경기 등에서, 기록에 남길 만한 일이 이루어지다.</dd><br>
<dd>A state in which something worthy of being recorded has been accomplished, as in sports games, etc.</dd><br>
<dt>작문 [장문]</dt><br>
<dd>1. writing; composition</dd><br>
<dd>글을 지음. 또는 지은 글.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of creating a written work; a written work.</dd><br>
<dd>2. writing; composition</dd><br>
<dd>학생이 자기의 감상이나 생각을 글로 쓰는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>A student's act of expressing his/her opinions or thoughts in writing.</dd><br>
<dt>쓰기 [쓰기]</dt><br>
<dd>writing</dd><br>
<dd>생각이나 느낌을 글로 표현하는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of expressing one's thought or feeling in the written language.</dd><br>
<dt>글짓기 [글짇끼]</dt><br>
<dd>writing</dd><br>
<dd>보통 학생들이 글 쓰는 실력을 기르기 위해 자신의 생각을 글로 쓰는 것.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of writing one's thoughts to develop writing skills, usually by students,</dd><br>
<dt>글씨 [글씨]</dt><br>
<dd>1. form of letters</dd><br>
<dd>써 놓은 글자의 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>The form in which characters are written.</dd><br>
<dd>2. letter; character</dd><br>
<dd>말을 적는 기호. 글자.</dd><br>
<dd>Symbols used for writing words; the characters.</dd><br>
<dd>3. way of writing; writing</dd><br>
<dd>글자를 쓰는 법이나 그런 일.</dd><br>
<dd>A system or act of writing characters.</dd><br>
<dt>글쓰기 [글쓰기]</dt><br>
<dd>writing</dd><br>
<dd>생각이나 사실 등을 글로 써서 표현하는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>Expressing a fact or one's thought by writing it down.</dd><br>
<dt>글 [글]</dt><br>
<dd>1. writing; text</dd><br>
<dd>생각이나 일 등의 내용을 글자로 나타낸 것.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of expressing one's thoughts or affairs in words.</dd><br>
<dd>2. learning; study</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 학문이나 학식.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) Learning and knowledge.</dd><br>
<dd>3. letter; character</dd><br>
<dd>말의 소리나 뜻을 나타내기 위한 기호, 또는 그런 기호들의 체계.</dd><br>
<dd>A symbol designed to indicate the sound or meaning of words; or a system of such symbols.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>